{"id": 232004748, "title": "This Morning star looks unrecognisable in throwback wedding snap", "text": "A This Morning star looks unrecognisable in his 51-year-old wedding photo (Picture: Gyles Brandreth/ Instagram) Gyles Brandreth has shared a sweet snap taken on his wedding day in 1973. The This Morning star, 76, has become known for his appearances on programmes including Countdown, Public Opinion, QI and Celebrity Gogglebox over the years. Since the 1970s he\u2019s also presented various radio shows and written books for both adults and children. From 1992 until 1997 he was also a Conservative MP, representing the City of Chester, while he\u2019s also become known for his colourful and humorous jumpers worn throughout his career in the public eye. But before all that, Gyles was a student at Oxford, where he not only studied Modern History and Modern Languages, but met his future wife, Michele Brown. Five years later, while he was working in theatre and she as a TV reporter, the couple decided to have a \u2018quiet wedding\u2019. Gyles Brandreth married his wife Michele in 1973 (Picture: Gyles Brandreth/ Instagram) They were married at Marylebone Register Office on June 8, 1973, with actor Simon Cadell, Brandreth\u2019s best friend from school, as a witness. This week Gyles shared a photograph from that day to mark 51 years since they tied the knot, with the presenter appearing somewhat unrecognisable. Wearing a pinstripe suit and thick dark tie, Gyles held his arm around the shoulder of his bride and rested his head on Michele, who was wearing a floral denim two-piece jacket and skirt set. The couple share four children (Picture: Jonathan Hordle/REX) \u2018\u201d A friend may well be reckoned the masterpiece of nature\u201d \u2013 Ralph Waldo Emerson,\u2019 he captioned the post. \u2018The picture is of me and my wife, Michele, outside Marylebone Register Office in London, on our wedding day: 8 June 1973,\u2019 he added. His followers sent many messages of support, with one exclaiming what a \u2018beautiful couple\u2019 they were. \u2018What a lovely photo! You look like the cat that\u2019s got the cream. Happy Anniversary!\u2019 Julia commented on the post. He is best known for appearing on TV shows including This Morning (Picture: Ken McKay/ ITV/ REX/ Shutterstock) \u2018She is extraordinarily beautiful, Gyles. As you are, of course,\u2019 Emma shared. \u2018Beautiful picture beautiful couple. Congratulations on your milestone together so lovely to see. Happy anniversary to you both,\u2019 Lesley added. The couple, who have lived in Barnes in Southwest London since 1986, share three children. One of them, Aphra, is a former Conservative councillor in Richmond and is currently running for the constituency of Chester South and Eddisbury in the 2024 general election. This Morning airs weekdays at 10am on ITV1. Got a story? If you\u2019ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page \u2013 we\u2019d love to hear from you.", "summary": "His hairstyle was very of the era!", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/06/09/this-morning-star-looks-unrecognisable-throwback-wedding-snap-20999062/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/SEI_208008108-0e30-e1717935974153.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 14:17:32", "author": "Pierra Willix", "authors": ["Pierra Willix"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.764}